<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7343> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7343" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In MRR 2.443, and Index, 577, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.372, no. 358, 83 B.C. This date makes it possible to suggest that he was also the father of M. Iuventius Laterensis (16), Pr. 51. Cicero's reference in Planc. 51 (quid imaginibus tuis, quid ornatissimo et optimo viro, patri tuo) implies attainment of senatorial and curule rank. (RS, MS-RP 1.282-283)[115]\n" .
